The article is about three nominations sent to the Senate. Troy D. Edgar from California has been nominated to be the Chief Financial Officer of the Department of Homeland Security, replacing Charles H. Fulghum. Edward W. Felten from New Jersey has been nominated for reappointment as a Member of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board for a term expiring on January 29, 2025. Michael O. Johanns from Nebraska has been nominated for reappointment as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation for a term of two years.